snippet.textDisplay: I love Coke Studio Pakistan..however, and I may be the only one, I miss the actual, live, non-heavy autotuned performances given by incredible artists in the studio. It feels like it has become more of a visual show with (still fantastic) performances- music videos, than the singing. It was/is the singing that set this show apart from anything else for me but yeah, not everybody can sing live as well as Abida Parveen, Rahat Fateh Ali Khan, Ali Sethi, just to name a few.
